  "response_text": "A human-sized Jack in the Box mascot walks toward the viewer along a sunny, tree-lined sidewalk in a public plaza or campus-like setting. He wears a blue suit, white shirt, and red tie, with the familiar oversized round white head, blue dot eyes, red smile, small black nose, and orange cone-shaped hat. In one hand he carries a long wrapped sandwich upright like something easy to hold while walking. People move in the background among lawns, benches, planters, and leafy trees.\n\nThe scene cuts to a dark tabletop product display. Two long toasted sandwiches sit on raised metal trays, one in front and one behind it. The front sandwich shows layers of deli meats, green vegetables, pale cheese, and red sauce inside a long ciabatta-style roll. A small green label beside it reads “Deli Trio.” The rear sandwich has pale turkey slices, orange cheddar, bacon, and red sauce, and a small red label appears above it reading “Turkey, Bacon & Cheddar.” Steam or heat haze rises faintly against the dark background, making the sandwiches look freshly toasted.\n\nJack is back on the sidewalk, still facing forward and holding the sandwich. The setting remains bright and green, with dappled shade from the trees. He stands centered and composed, as if demonstrating a good way to eat while on the move. A large green check mark appears near the bottom with bold green text reading “PANNI-DO.”\n\nNow Jack sits inside a red convertible car, seen through the windshield. His round smiling head is visible behind the glass, and he holds the sandwich in one hand while seated in the driver’s area. The same green check mark and “PANNI-DO” text appears, indicating eating in the car is acceptable.\n\nThe commercial shifts to a city street outside storefronts. A light blue sedan drives past, and behind it a woman in a bright blue suit appears on top of a car, standing with her feet wide apart and arms spread. She holds a sandwich in one hand and seems to be energetically posing or dancing on the car roof. As she moves, low tree branches hang over her. A red X and bold red text “PANNI-DON’T” appear across the bottom. She gets tangled or knocked by the branches and disappears downward from view behind the car roof, making the action look like a bad idea.\n\nJack then exits a dry cleaner’s shop through a teal-framed doorway. He still wears his suit and holds the sandwich while also carrying clothing over one shoulder, possibly a garment bag or jacket. The shop windows show signs including “Alterations,” “Stain Removal,” “Wedding Gowns,” and a large diamond-shaped “Cleaners” logo. A green check mark and “PANNI-DO” appear at the bottom, marking this errand-running version as acceptable.\n\nIn a grassy park, a man in a blue sweater and olive pants stands holding a sandwich in one hand and looking down at a smartphone in the other. Trees, benches, paths, and pedestrians fill the background. From the right, a football player in a red-and-white uniform charges in low and tackles him around the waist. As the player collides with him, a red X and “PANNI-DON’T” appear at the bottom, turning the joke on the idea of being “tackled.”\n\nJack sits at an outdoor café table on a city sidewalk. He has a small open laptop or tablet on the round wooden table, along with a potted plant, and he holds the sandwich in one hand while facing the screen. Cars and pedestrians pass in the background. A green check mark and “PANNI-DO” label appear, suggesting working at a café table while eating is fine.\n\nA close view shows a large black boombox with speakers, buttons, tape decks, and sliders sitting outdoors near orange traffic cones. A gloved hand reaches in and presses a button. The setting widens to a construction site with barricades, cones, caution tape, a stop sign, dust or steam, construction equipment, and several workers in hard hats and orange safety vests. Jack stands calmly in the foreground holding his sandwich while workers move energetically around him, including one on equipment in the background and another near the boombox. At first a red X with “PANNI-DON’T” appears over the construction scene. After a moment, the on-screen judgment changes to a green check mark and “PANNI-DO,” while Jack remains smiling in front of the busy work zone.\n\nThe commercial ends on a dark product card. The two long sandwiches return on metal trays, with steam rising around them. Large red text at the top reads “New PANNIDOS,” and the small labels identify the varieties as “Deli Trio” and “Turkey, Bacon & Cheddar.” Fine print appears along the bottom, too small to read clearly.",
